tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE medical_devices (
  device_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  device_name VARCHAR(255),
  manufacturer VARCHAR(255),
  maintenance_schedule VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE maintenance_schedules (
  schedule_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  device_id INT,
  maintenance_date DATE,
  maintenance_notes TEXT,
  FOREIGN KEY (device_id) REFERENCES medical_devices(device_id)
);

CREATE TABLE maintenance_schedule (
    schedule_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    device_id INT,
    maintenance_date DATE,
    maintenance_notes TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (device_id) REFERENCES medical_devices(device_id)
);

CREATE TABLE maintenance_schedules (
  schedule_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  device_id UUID REFERENCES medical_devices(device_id),
  schedule_date DATE,
  technician_name VARCHAR(255),
  maintenance_type VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE medical_devices (
  device_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  device_name VARCHAR(255),
  manufacturer VARCHAR(255),
  purchase_date DATE,
  maintenance_schedule VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE maintenance_logs (
  log_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  device_id INT,
  maintenance_date DATE,
  technician VARCHAR(255),
  maintenance_type VARCHAR(255),
  maintenance_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE technicians (
  technician_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  technician_name VARCHAR(255),
  technician_specialty VARCHAR(255),
  technician_certification VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE devices_history (
  history_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  device_id INT,
  event_type VARCHAR(255),
  event_date DATE,
  event_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE maintenance_schedule (
  schedule_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  device_id INT,
  schedule_type VARCHAR(255),
  schedule_interval INTERVAL,
  last_maintenance_date DATE
)
